place_description: Tega Cay Coffee Company is open for business! We are happy to announce our storefront at 1177 Stonecrest Blvd - We look forward to serving you the absolute best coffee around!

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place, been going since they were in the trailer! My kids love it as well!
Favorite coffee spot hands down.
The Drunken Cupid February special latte was delicious and the bacon, egg and cheese burrito was one of the best I've had. Great spot to grab breakfast and coffee with friends.
This is a great spot for food, drinks and atmosphere. Everything on the menu is very good, my personal favorites are the breakfast burritos, breakfast biscuits and the brown sugar cinnamon latte.
Great service. Love having a local shop like this.
Love this coffee shop. Also try the reverse cons brew for the best cup of coffee you can ever get!

I absolutely love this coffee spot! From the moment you walk in, the cozy atmosphere and friendly staff make you feel right at home. The coffee is always rich and flavorful, and they have a fantastic selection of pastries that pair perfectly with each cup. Whether I'm here for a quiet morning or meeting friends, it's always a relaxing experience. The attention to detail in both the drinks and the service really stands out. Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great coffee and a welcoming vibe! And the best part is it's locally owned!
Great coffee, great service, great owner!  Must visit in Tega Cay!

DELICIOUS coffee that caters to everyone's preferenes. served and owned by people who genuinely value their customers. Whether it's a hot coffee (I prefer Skipper's Signature) served black, or a cold brew/iced cofee/latte, it ALWAYS hits the spot. They have effectively ruined my taste buds because no other coffee hits the same for me anymore. I also love trying their new and always unique flavor combos that their workers come up with (posted on one of their blackboards).  Everyone that works there is great, especially Skipper their doggy mascot who is almost always there and ready to welcome you in exchange for belly rubs.

Well I think I'm just gonna delete my Dunkin and Starbucks apps because this is absolutely the best Iced Chai I have ever had! I added vanilla and caramel....the first sip was heavenly!!!! Exactly what I needed to start my day!!!! Def my go to coffee shop now!!! Service was also quick and friendly!!!!

The baristas here are always so kind and welcoming. Me and my roommate love coming here and trying different flavors. I love how they let you customize the sweetness. I like doing 1/2 sweet pistachio.
Absolutely Amazing
Best coffee in town. An amazing and necessary addition to Tega Cay. Love to watch them grow from a mobile trailer to a brick and mortar shop that is busy on the weekends!

Great coffee and food! We are big fans of the breakfast burritos, and bagels are great as well. Staff is also always friendly. Space is kind of cramped, but we're local so totally okay with taking home (or to work) to enjoy! Also very reasonably priced. Love this spot!

I was feeling the need to get out of the house this morning and so I brought my laptop with me to work from here for a couple of hours. I arrived at 7:30 and found that I wasn't the only person doing so.

A friendly barista made a pretty decent cortado though served in a paper cup. Two shots of espresso and the equivalent amount of milk which is steamed rather than foamed. This was good stuff.

They do not have a drive thru so there's a pretty consistent parade of people coming and going for their morning coffee. They also have bagels and burritos and pastries. This was a pleasant morning and a really nice coffee shop.
Amazing coffee, staff, and food!
very delightful!
Excellent coffee. Latte was just right!
Best coffee place in the area and the breakfast options are always great!  Friendly staff and welcoming atmosphere!  A great addition to Tega Cay
Pretty solid coffee.
Awesome seasonal flavors and high quality expresso!
Everyone is always kind and eager to help. Best coffee I have had. Will recommend.
Amazing coffee and cute seating area!
Im a huge fan of Tega Cay Coffee. Their coffee is the best in town & I come here several times a week!

Definitely the best place to get a cup of coffee, sit and hang out, grab a quick bite, or even have a quick meeting. Yes I've done all of these and I love coming back. The staff is super nice and the drinks are always quick to come out. I've been coming here since they were just a small trailer and now they have their own store front in Tega cay! So cool to see a local business grow and succeed. Give them a try!
Great coffee shop with pleasant atmosphere and good prices.
Great coffee!!
Es un lugar super agradable, la chica que atiende es amable, probe cafe caliente, cafe frio y un bagel divino la verdad !! Recomendados
Chai latte made my Bri was best I've ever had!  Great Job!
My favorite coffee place

I'm often leave positive reviews and especially to small businesses, but my experience here was horrible. When I walked in, the person taking my order was rude and did not effectively answer my question about the menu. I ordered a blueberry cobbler latte and it tasted good. I had originally planned to stay to charge my phone (from the power outage - Helene) and read on my kindle, but the space was a little cramped and I was extremely put off by the customer service. With a plethora of good, independent coffee shops in the area, I will not be back here.
I adore the coffee. Furthermore, the apple cider chai blew my mind! Simply phenomenal.
My favorite local coffee shop. The breakfast burritos and cold brew are delicious!
Amazing !

I literally drive from Rock Hill multiple times a week. Their coffee, espresso, drink options and breakfast wraps are unmatched. They also do great breakfast sandwiches on many options. Do yourself a favor and give them a try, you won't be disappointed. The atmosphere is cute, parking is easy & staff are great. Family owned and an easy small business to support!
Cold Brew coffee was delicious! Highly recommend their coffee if you are looking for nicely made homemade coffee.

The first time I came here I asked for an iced chai latte, they asked if I wanted any flavorings and I said sure, caramel. They asked syrup or drizzle. I said dealers choices. It was delicious and beautiful! The second time, today, I asked for a pumpkin iced chai latte. They said they don't have that yet but they can do an apple cinnamon one- the baristas started to go back and forth about how that was only for them? (Idk, associates only I imagine trying flavors before launch) and it was awkward. Then what I was given but just straight up milk. I watched them prepare my husband and i's drinks and it was really disappointing. Especially because we've been going to this place since it was just a little truck.
Delicious lattes and fun flavors. The customer service is great too.
Barista was chill. Greeted me from the door and made me feel special. Tall order done quick..7-3 everyday. Tha k you

So so good. Great coffee with awesome flavors available. Love trying out new flavors featured on the coffee specials menu that changes from time to time. The food is also amazing and freshly prepared. I love the spicy southwest burrito especially. It ends up being two meals for me because it's so big. The decor is nice and it's a comfy place to enjoy your coffee or meal while catching up with a friend.
Coffee is good. Service is slow. It would be nice if drip coffee could be served yourself.  Waiting for 10 specialty drinks to be made before they pump my drip coffee is frustrating at times.
The seasonal drinks are always the best. The bananas foster latte is divine. I'm so happy that the storefront opened, it's even closer to my house.
Intimate space with kind staff, excellent drinks and phenomenal food!
Love this place. Really quality coffee and great service. They also always have fun special and seasonal drinks. So happy they have a new location.

Finally a locally owned coffee shop within walking distance from home. They just opened about 3 weeks ago. Its Stonecrest Blvd across the street from mynkid's preschool, The Learning Experience and very close Model A.

Its a very nice place. Friendly staff,  coffee is excellent and so are the breakfast burritos. Highly recommend it.
The best coffee I have ever had! I usually don't take the time to leave reviews but this deserves 5 stars! The convenience of ordering online is also a plus!!

Finally tried tega cay coffee and glad I did. Ordered the hot oat-milk chai latte and it was heavenly. Loved every sip. I also ordered the vegan egg & cheese pocket and it was ok. Not as good as everything else on the menu. Will be coming back here to support local businesses instead of going to Starbucks.
The shop was clean, cool, and the staff were very chill.

Got this little cup of hot chai and an apple crisp bar on the go. Whoa! First of all, best hot chai latte I've ever had! There is no picture of the apple bar because it was so delicious, it disappeared before I could get a photo! Thank you!
Great coffee and tasty baked goods!
Kid friendly and awesome staff!!! Their flavors are good and fast service. This is a go to place for fresh coffee and service.
Cute coffee stand.  They have a nice outside sitting area as well and the workers are very nice
We visited the truck on a whim and we are glad we did. The coffee was very good. It was very affordable.
Tried the breakfast burrito .  It was fantastic, piping hot and delicious!!  Paired it with the Lucky Leprechaun Speciality Coffee FTW..
Friendly and great flavors
They are the best! Always so friendly and serve the best drinks!

The CUTEST little coffee food truck. Got a pumpkin latte and waffle. The pumpkin flavor is homemade and not too sweet. There is also a little spot off to the side to enjoy your coffee in the nice weather.
This was my first visit to Tega Cay Coffee. The service was great and the coffee and food were very good as well. We will visit again and recommend trying Tega Cay Coffee.
It's Mike, the big guy that always makes jokes. Nice hidden gem. Couldn't be a better location for me. Beats Starbucks and Dunkin's service.
Nice little hidden gem in Tega Cay. The coffee was great and the baristas were super friendly
Super cool little spot, and some delicious coffee. Great people too. :)
The coffee shop is excellent. The staff was so friendly.  LOVED IT!!
Excellent coffee spot hidden away off the beaten path.  Big bold flavors are served up from the mobile shop that has an established seating area just behind it!
This is a little hidden gem. It's a food truck that's stationary in the parking lot next to the building. They have great coffee and treats. Very reasonably priced. Highly recommend!

We love to visit the shop during the week. Whenever we visit and there's a particular girl working the coffee is really not good and the service is always pretty off. She just typically always has something to complain about and we never finish our coffee because it's just not made well. We will avoid going whenever she works. Definitely a waste of money today
Great coffee, great service!
Super cute place! Coffee was very fresh tasting- I like mine sweeter so I'll ask for more next time, but very good flavor! And very friendly baristas!
Phenomenal coffee spot. Came here once to try it out and ended up coming back every day while in town. Would highly recommend.
Our favorite coffee hands down!!! We were looking for a great place for coffee beans and drinks when we moved here a year ago. Great staff, great service - we love it!
A jewel of a place! The coffee is great and even though it's a good truck it has terrific outdoor seating. Highly recommend. Fort Mills best kept secret!
Great cafe au lait and very cute coffee truck.
Great coffee and friendly people working there.
Wish they had a building but the coffee is definitely amazing and I will keep coming back.
Great coffee! Always tastes fresh!
My absolute favorite coffee spot!

My fiance and I followed the recommendation of our close friends and we are SO glad we did!! We are at Tega Cay Coffee at least 3 times a week and it is more than worth the 10 minute drive from our house. The staff is always so kind and remembers our regular order & our dog's name- they also have a friendly dog named Skipper that is typically there too!
Our favorite is the cold brew coffee with cream and variations of vanilla syrups. Once the weather is cooler, we're excited to try new hot coffee drinks. The baked goods that they offer are always SO yummy.
We are so happy to have found this local gem of a coffee shop and will always support them! :)
Love a Tega Cay coffee! Highly recommend if you're looking for great service and fantastic coffee!
This is our favorite coffee place in town. Make sure to try the concentrate they offer.
they have the best iced lattes ever. perfectly balanced between espresso and the milk. HIGHLY RECOMMEND IF YOU WANT REALLY GOOD COFFEE AND WELL PRICED.

This was the best coffee I've had since I found a local farm on the big island of Hawaii back in March. Zero, I mean zero bitterness!!! Killer flavor!!! Added an espresso shot, cream and a stevia but the sweetener after drinking it wasn't even needed...

To begin, the baristas were super sweet and there was no line when I ordered so that was great! However, I wasn't a fan of the waffle or drink. The waffle was just ok and the coffee could have been better. It may have been what I ordered so I will give another try with the blueberry cobbler coffee that is on their menu.

Tried to get my wife a nice Mother's Day treat before church. I beat the barista there. No prob. Decided to wait. As you can see in my picture at 8:10 she still hasn't opened the store. Had to leave to make it to church on time. Needless to say very disappointed. Time to find. New coffee shop!!!
Best coffee and waffles! The service is great too. Catch them early. They have limited hours.
Great coffee and delicious waffles! Found our new favorite place to get coffee and sweet treats
Love all the flavor combos. Delicious pick me up. Best coffee around.
Awesome spot and great service. Enjoyed visiting and hanging out in the seating area. Great suggestions for drinks.
Their coffees are great!
Best coffee in town! I love the seasonal options and recommendations!
Sure you can go to Starbucks, but drive the extra mile down the road and support a great local business! The staff are always friendly, the coffee is great and the service is fast.
Sweet girls and great coffee! It's behind Keller Williams!! Highly recommend!
Barista was spot on with her recommendation! Really enjoyed the coffee and hope to visit again soon.
This is our go to place every Sunday before we take the dogs for a walk. Great people and coffee. I'd rather support a local, family owned business than Starbucks or Dunkin any day.
So many delicious options! Thanks for adding the waffles, they're amazing! Favorite thing I've tried so far - iced dirty chai latte, so good!!
Amazing coffee and service!! Will be coming here weekly!

Tega Cay Coffee offers a high level of customer service.  I have been very impressed by the speed of response to online orders, the ease of local delivery, and the thoughtful consideration given to my questions about the different roasts.  I have been meaning to stop by their location on Dave Gibson Blvd but haven't yet had the chance, but now I am going to make time to stop by this week.  Highly recommended!
Owner reached out and gave great customer service and tasty coffee. They truly care for their customers and strive to make great coffee

I love this place so much! The owners truly care about their customers and are always looking for ways to collab with local businesses! ++ in my books because supporting local is the best!
Their coffee is crafted with passion to bring a unique experience for the customer and tastes AMAZING. They offer a variety of flavor options. My favorite is the Iced White Chocolate Raspberry latte with skim milk!
Now on to the baristas! They are always genuinely happy and provide customers with the best customer service. I never feel like 'another transaction'. It's nice to have a local coffee place in Tega Cay / Fort Mill with great products and friendly customer service!
Thanks Tega Cay Coffee Co. for all you do!

Love this place SO much! The coffee is amazing (I have purchased the coffee at the truck and also the bags to brew at home) and the people are so so friendly. They always have such fun flavors...the oatmeal cookie latte they had a few months ago was AMAZING  They're the best!

Honestly, there's something to be desired with this coffee. They're now in a permanent location next to Keller Williams Fort Mill offices. They offer the basic normal flavors and I didn't see any special lattes on the menu. I just ordered a vanilla latte and a caramel latte and honestly it tasted like something I can make at home. There was no unique flavor to the coffee. With so many coffee shops and coffee trucks these days, you have to do something to stand out. Offering some unique flavored lattes is one way to do that.
